10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-97 of Title 2, unless there is
13 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary, for any pesticide
15 registered with the United States Environmental Protection Agency
16 under the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act, 7
17 U.S.C., Section 136 et seq., the label approved by the United States
18 Environmental Protection Agency in registering the pesticide, or a
19 label consistent with the most recent human health assessment
20 performed under the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide
21 Act, or a label consistent with the United States Environmental
22 Protection Agency carcinogenicity classification for the pesticide
23 under the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act, shall
24 be sufficient to satisfy any requirements for a warning regarding
